55.9	Kiln	Kiln	A kiln is a thermally insulated chamber, or oven, in which a controlled temperature regime is produced. Uses include the hardening, burning or drying of materials. Kilns are also used for the firing of materials, such as clay and other raw materials, to form ceramics (including pottery, bricks etc.).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Charcoal_Kilns%2C_California.JPG/250px-Charcoal_Kilns%2C_California.JPG
